"Vous devriez aussi activer quelques modules "
"<application>lighttpd</application> pour utiliser <application>Ruby on "
"Rails</application>. Vous pouvez lancer les commandes suivantes pour activer "
"ces modules :"

#: ../generic/server/C/web-servers.xml:1040(programlisting) ../generic/serverguide/C/web-servers.xml:1040(programlisting)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"sudo /usr/sbin/lighty-enable-mod fastcgi\n"
"sudo /usr/sbin/lighty-enable-mod proxy\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"sudo /usr/sbin/lighty-enable-mod fastcgi\n"
"sudo /usr/sbin/lighty-enable-mod proxy\n"

#: ../generic/server/C/web-servers.xml:1045(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/web-servers.xml:1045(para)
msgid ""
"Let us now verify the modification we did in the "
"<filename>/etc/lighttpd/lighttpd.conf</filename> configuration file. Run the "
"following commands to stop and verify the modification:"
