#: ../generic/server/C/network-auth.xml:256(title) ../generic/serverguide/C/network-auth.xml:256(title)
msgid "LDAP replication"
msgstr "Réplication LDAP"

#: ../generic/server/C/network-auth.xml:258(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/network-auth.xml:258(para)
msgid ""
"LDAP service often quickly becomes a highly critical service in an "
"information system: all is depending of LDAP: autentication, authorization, "
"mail system, etc. It is a good idea to setup a redundant system. It is easy "
"to setup, and here is a quick howto."
msgstr ""
"Le service d'annuaire LDAP devient souvent rapidement un service hautement "
"critique dans un système d'information : tout dépend de LDAP : "
"l'authentification, les autorisations, la messagerie, etc. Configurer un "
"système redondant est donc une bonne idée que l'on peut de surcroit "
"facilement mettre en œuvre comme le montre la petite explication suivante."

#: ../generic/server/C/network-auth.xml:265(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/network-auth.xml:265(para)
msgid ""
"Replication will be based here on a master-slave relation. Before "
"implementing LDAP replication consider the following steps:"
msgstr ""
"La réplication sera basée ici sur une relation maître-esclave. Avant de "
"mettre en œuvre la réplication LDAP, vérifiez les étapes suivantes :"

#: ../generic/server/C/network-auth.xml:272(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/network-auth.xml:272(para)
msgid "Stop the master server's slapd daemon."
msgstr "Arrêter le démon slapd du serveur maître."

#: ../generic/server/C/network-auth.xml:275(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/network-auth.xml:275(para)
msgid ""
"Reconfigure the master server's slapd.conf to enable replication to the new "
"slave server."
msgstr ""
"Reconfigurer le fichier slapd.conf du serveur maître afin de permettre la "
"réplication sur le nouveau serveur esclave."

#: ../generic/server/C/network-auth.xml:279(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/network-auth.xml:279(para)
msgid "Export the database of the master server."
msgstr "Exporter la base de données du serveur maître."

#: ../generic/server/C/network-auth.xml:282(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/network-auth.xml:282(para)
msgid "Configure the replica server's <filename>slapd.conf</filename>."
msgstr ""
"Configurer le fichier <filename>slapd.conf</filename> du serveur réplica."

#: ../generic/server/C/network-auth.xml:286(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/network-auth.xml:286(para)
msgid "Import the database of the master server to the slaver server."
msgstr ""
"Importer la base de données du serveur maître sur le serveur esclave."

#: ../generic/server/C/network-auth.xml:290(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/network-auth.xml:290(para)
msgid "Re/Start the replica server's slapd process"
msgstr "(Re)démarrer le processus slapd du serveur réplica"

#: ../generic/server/C/network-auth.xml:293(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/network-auth.xml:293(para)
msgid "Re/Start the master server's slapd process."
msgstr "Redémarrer le processus slapd du serveur maître"

#: ../generic/server/C/network-auth.xml:297(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/network-auth.xml:297(para)
msgid ""
"You will have to remember that modifications should ALWAYS be done on the "
"master. If you modify the slave, they will get lost."
msgstr ""
"Vous devez vous rappeler que les modifications doivent TOUJOURS être "
"apportées sur le serveur maître. Si par mégarde vous modifiez le serveur "
"esclave, vos modifications seront perdues."

#: ../generic/server/C/network-auth.xml:303(title) ../generic/serverguide/C/network-auth.xml:303(title)
msgid "LDAP Master"
msgstr "Maître LDAP"

#: ../generic/server/C/network-auth.xml:305(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/network-auth.xml:305(para)
msgid ""
"On the master, you have to modify the database section of the "
"<filename>/etc/ldap/slapd.conf</filename> to add a replica instruction. The "
"following example shows a replica on ldap-2.example.com with the Manager "
"user with secret as password. The replication logfile is the place "
"modifications are stored before they are send to the LDAP slave."
msgstr ""
"Sur le serveur maître, vous devez modifier la section base de données du "
"fichier <filename>/etc/ldap/slapd.conf</filename> pour ajouter une "
"instruction de réplication. L'exemple suivant permet une réplication sur "
"ldap-2.example.com avec l'utilisateur « Manager » et le mot de passe « "
"secret ». Le journal de réplication contient les modifications effectuées "
"avant qu'elles ne soient envoyées au serveur LDAP esclave."

#: ../generic/server/C/network-auth.xml:313(programlisting) ../generic/serverguide/C/network-auth.xml:313(programlisting)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"replica uri=ldap://ldap-2.example.com:389 "
"binddn=\"cn=Manager,dc=example,dc=com\" bindmethod=simple "
"credentials=secret\n"
"\n"
"replogfile      /var/lib/ldap/replog\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"replica uri=ldap://ldap-2.example.com:389 "
"binddn=\"cn=Manager,dc=example,dc=com\" bindmethod=simple "
"credentials=secret\n"
"\n"
"replogfile      /var/lib/ldap/replog\n"

#: ../generic/server/C/network-auth.xml:319(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/network-auth.xml:319(para)
msgid ""
"Export the database of the master using slapcat. Then copy master.ldif to "
"the slave using scp or other tools."
msgstr ""
"Exportez la base de données du maître à l'aide de slapcat. Puis copiez "
"master.ldif sur l'esclave à l'aide de scp ou d'autres outils."

#: ../generic/server/C/network-auth.xml:324(programlisting) ../generic/serverguide/C/network-auth.xml:324(programlisting)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"user@master:~$ sudo slapcat -l master.ldif\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"user@master:~$ sudo slapcat -l master.ldif\n"

#: ../generic/server/C/network-auth.xml:331(title) ../generic/serverguide/C/network-auth.xml:331(title)
msgid "LDAP Slave"
msgstr "Esclave LDAP"

#: ../generic/server/C/network-auth.xml:333(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/network-auth.xml:333(para)
msgid ""
"On the slave, you have to authorize your master to update LDAP database. Add "
"the following lines to your <filename>/etc/ldap/slapd.conf</filename> file "
"in the database section:"
msgstr ""
"Sur l'esclave, vous devez autoriser votre maître à mettre à jour la base de "
"données LDAP. Ajoutez les lignes suivantes à votre fichier "
"<filename>/etc/ldap/slapd.conf</filename> dans la section 'database' :"

#: ../generic/server/C/network-auth.xml:339(programlisting) ../generic/serverguide/C/network-auth.xml:339(programlisting)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"updatedn        cn=Manager,dc=example,dc=com\n"
"updateref       ldap://ldap-1.example.com\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"updatedn        cn=Manager,dc=example,dc=com\n"
"updateref       ldap://ldap-1.example.com\n"

#: ../generic/server/C/network-auth.xml:344(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/network-auth.xml:344(para)
msgid "Import the <filename>master.ldif</filename> using slapadd."
msgstr ""
"Importez le fichier <filename>master.ldif</filename> à l'aide de slapadd."

#: ../generic/server/C/network-auth.xml:348(programlisting) ../generic/serverguide/C/network-auth.xml:348(programlisting)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"user@slave:~$ sudo slapadd -c -l master.ldif\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"user@slave:~$ sudo slapadd -c -l master.ldif\n"

#: ../generic/server/C/network-auth.xml:352(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/network-auth.xml:352(para)
msgid "Restart the master server."
msgstr "Redémarrer le serveur maître."

#: ../generic/server/C/network-auth.xml:356(programlisting) ../generic/serverguide/C/network-auth.xml:356(programlisting)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"user@master:~$ sudo /etc/init.d/slapd start\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"user@master:~$ sudo /etc/init.d/slapd start\n"

#: ../generic/server/C/network-auth.xml:360(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/network-auth.xml:360(para)
msgid "Restart the slave server."
msgstr "Rédémarrer le serveur esclave."

#: ../generic/server/C/network-auth.xml:364(programlisting) ../generic/serverguide/C/network-auth.xml:364(programlisting)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"user@slave:~$ sudo /etc/init.d/slapd start\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"user@slave:~$ sudo /etc/init.d/slapd start\n"

